results.title: A Local's Guide to Travel in Galicia, Spain
results.content: Isolated by the mountains on its eastern border, Galicia and Gallegos have always leaned towards the Atlantic Ocean, so it’s along the coast that you’ll find the three main cities, which form the backbone of the region: A Coruña, Santiago de Compostela, and Vigo. Galicia is filled with wonderful places to visit, offering a mix of cities, villages, islands, beaches, mountains, and more. If you're not in the mood for a big city but still want to experience the power of the Galician sea, and perhaps try *percebes*, the most famous seafood in Galicia (people in Madrid and Barcelona pay thousands of euros for it), then I'll let you in on a little secret: the village of O Barqueiro, on the north coast of A Coruña. A Coruña is the most fun city in Galicia, if not in all of Spain, and here are some hints for you to enjoy its day-to-day life like a true local.
